@startuml Post_Liking_Sequence_Detailed
!theme blueprint
title Post Liking System - User Interaction & Synchronization

actor User as U
participant "Frontend UI\n(PostList/PostDetail)" as FE
participant "Posts Store\n(Pinia State)" as PS
participant "API Client\n(HTTP Service)" as API
participant "Backend API\n(api.localtest.me:3001)" as BE
database "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as DB

== Phase 1: Initial Post Display ==
U -> FE: 1. View posts interface
note right: User navigates to blog posts

FE -> PS: 2. Load posts from store
PS -> API: 3. GET /api/posts
note right
**API Request:**
- URL: api.localtest.me:3001/api/posts
- Method: GET
- Headers: Authorization Bearer token
- Response: Posts with like counts
end note

API -> BE: 4. HTTP Request with authentication
BE -> DB: 5. SELECT posts with likes_count

DB --> BE: 6. Posts with like counts & user status
BE --> API: 7. JSON response with posts
API --> PS: 8. Posts data array
PS --> FE: 9. Update reactive posts state
FE -> U: 10. Display posts with like counts

== Phase 2: Like/Unlike Interaction ==
U -> FE: 11. Click like button on post
note right: User toggles like on specific post

FE -> FE: 12. Optimistic UI update
note right
**Optimistic Update Logic:**
const optimisticUpdate = () => {
  post.is_liked = !post.is_liked
  post.likes_count += post.is_liked ? 1 : -1
}
**Benefits:**
- Instant visual feedback
- Better user experience
- Rollback on error
end note

FE -> PS: 13. likePost(postId)
PS -> API: 14. toggleLike(postId)
API -> BE: 15. POST /api/posts/:id/like
note right
**API Request Details:**
- URL: /api/posts/{uuid}/like
- Method: POST
- Headers: Authorization Bearer token
- Body: Empty (toggle action)
end note

== Phase 3: Backend Processing & Database Operations ==
BE -> BE: 16. Validate session & extract user
note right
**Authentication Validation:**
const session = await validateSession(
  request.headers.authorization ||
  request.headers['x-session-id'] ||
  request.cookies.session
);
**Security Checks:**
- Bearer token validation
- Session expiry check
- User existence verification
end note

alt Session Valid & User Authenticated
    BE -> DB: 17. Check existing like status
    note right
    **Like Status Query:**
    SELECT EXISTS(
      SELECT 1 FROM post_likes 
      WHERE post_id = $1 AND user_id = $2
    ) as is_liked;
    end note
    
    DB --> BE: 18. Current like status
    
    alt User hasn't liked post yet
        BE -> DB: 19a. INSERT INTO post_likes
        note right
        **Database Trigger Fires:**
        - Automatically increments posts.likes_count
        - Maintains data consistency
        end note
        
        DB -> DB: 20a. Trigger updates posts.likes_count (+1)
        BE -> DB: 21a. SELECT updated post data
        DB --> BE: 22a. Post with new like count
        
    else User has already liked post
        BE -> DB: 19b. DELETE FROM post_likes
        note right
        **Database Trigger Fires:**
        - Automatically decrements posts.likes_count
        - Maintains referential integrity
        end note
        
        DB -> DB: 20b. Trigger updates posts.likes_count (-1)
        BE -> DB: 21b. SELECT updated post data
        DB --> BE: 22b. Post with updated like count
    end
    
    BE --> API: 23. Success response with updated post
    note right
    **API Response:**
    {
      "success": true,
      "data": {
        "id": "uuid",
        "likes_count": 42,
        "is_liked": true
      },
      "message": "Post like toggled successfully"
    }
    end note
    
    API --> PS: 24. Updated post data
    PS -> PS: 25. Update local post state
    PS -> FE: 26. Sync like state across components
    FE -> U: 27. Show final like state
    
else Session Invalid or Expired
    BE --> API: 23b. 401 Unauthorized
    note right
    **Error Response:**
    {
      "success": false,
      "message": "Authentication required",
      "error": "UNAUTHORIZED"
    }
    end note
    
    API --> PS: 24b. Authentication error
    PS -> FE: 25b. Rollback optimistic update
    PS -> FE: 26b. Show authentication error
    FE -> U: 27b. Display login required message
end

== Phase 4: Component Synchronization ==
PS -> PS: 28. Update selectedPost (computed property)
note right
**Reactive Synchronization:**
const selectedPost = computed(() => 
  posts.value.find(p => p.id === selectedPostId.value)
);
end note

PS -> FE: 29. Trigger Vue reactivity
FE -> FE: 30. PostDetail reflects PostList changes
FE -> U: 31. Consistent like state across all views

@enduml
